<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--This is where all the colors are referenced at (Sorry for all the messiness, I'm not very good at
coming up with color names that makes sense lol)

To apply a color to a layout you'd use a command that looks something like this:

android:background="?attr/bgColor"

Or for text:

android:textColor="?attr/textColor"

Or for a drawable you'd just reference an @drawable in "styles.xml" and apply it like this:

android:src="?attr/logoColor"
-->

